WEBVTT

00:10.949 --> 00:12.143
<i>How did l get here?</i>

00:12.189 --> 00:14.703
<i>l turned around and there you were</i>

00:14.749 --> 00:17.388
<i>l didn't think twice or rationalise</i>

00:17.429 --> 00:20.501
<i>'cause somehow l knew</i>

00:20.549 --> 00:21.664
<i>That there was more...</i>

00:21.709 --> 00:26.829
Man, Miley is so lucky.
Her voice is so pure and natural and...

00:26.869 --> 00:30.464
<i>But l figured it's too good to be...</i>

00:32.069 --> 00:34.060
Okay, l know
l had a chilli dog for lunch,

00:34.109 --> 00:36.907
but there is no way that's me.

00:36.949 --> 00:38.382
Lola...

00:38.429 --> 00:40.067
Sorry! My bad.

00:44.509 --> 00:47.387
<i>You're one in a million</i>

00:47.429 --> 00:50.580
<i>Oh, yeah</i>

00:51.469 --> 00:52.822
<i>How'd that sound, Dad?</i>

00:52.869 --> 00:54.302
<i>Perfect.</i>

00:54.989 --> 00:57.139
That is such a great song!

00:57.189 --> 00:59.100
Have l told you
it's my mom's favourite?

00:59.149 --> 01:02.186
Hey, here's a wacky idea!
Her birthday's coming up.

01:02.229 --> 01:05.221
Maybe you could make
a special kind of personal recording,

01:05.269 --> 01:08.341
and l could give it to her as a present?

01:08.389 --> 01:11.222
You spent all her gift money
on those shoes, didn't you?

01:11.269 --> 01:13.863
They didn't have them in her size.

01:13.909 --> 01:17.618
l hear you. Last Christmas,
l bought Daddy these earrings.

01:18.629 --> 01:21.462
-See? This is why we're friends.
-Exactly.

01:21.509 --> 01:23.181
So, you'll do it? You'll record the song?

01:23.229 --> 01:24.787
Nope, you will.

01:26.829 --> 01:28.660
You're not kidding.

01:28.709 --> 01:33.464
No, kidding is when l tell my dad that
he looks good in that dorky moustache.

01:33.509 --> 01:35.898
<i>Your mike's still on, darling.</i>

01:36.469 --> 01:37.902
Love you!

01:39.349 --> 01:43.945
Lilly, to really make this special,
you're gonna have to record the song.

01:43.989 --> 01:45.627
But l don't have a voice like yours.

01:45.669 --> 01:49.059
You'll be surprised what you can
sound like in a professional studio.

01:49.109 --> 01:51.339
Trust me, you're gonna sound great.

01:51.389 --> 01:52.617
Okay.

01:53.709 --> 01:57.418
<i>One in a million</i>

02:00.949 --> 02:03.543
So, do you think my mom will like it?

02:04.069 --> 02:05.787
<i>Like it?</i>

02:05.829 --> 02:08.866
<i>She's gonna be speechless,
right, Dad?</i>

02:10.749 --> 02:12.421
<i>You see?</i>

02:20.149 --> 02:21.821
<i>come on!</i>

02:21.869 --> 02:25.862
<i>You get the limo out front</i>

02:25.909 --> 02:29.458
<i>Hottest styles, every shoe
every colour</i>

02:29.509 --> 02:33.138
<i>Yeah, when you're famous
it can be kind of fun</i>

02:33.189 --> 02:38.058
<i>lt's really you
but no one ever discovers</i>

02:38.109 --> 02:41.579
<i>Who would have thought
that a girl like me</i>

02:41.629 --> 02:45.019
<i>Would double as a superstar?</i>

02:47.029 --> 02:50.908
<i>You get the best of both worlds</i>

02:50.949 --> 02:52.985
<i>chill it out, take it slow</i>

02:53.029 --> 02:54.781
<i>Then you rock out the show</i>

02:54.829 --> 02:58.947
<i>You get the best of both worlds</i>

02:58.989 --> 03:00.661
<i>Mix it all together</i>

03:00.709 --> 03:03.826
<i>And you know that
it's the best of both worlds</i>

03:08.149 --> 03:11.141
<i>They say that good things take time</i>

03:13.389 --> 03:18.019
<i>But really great things happen
in the blink of an eye</i>

03:18.069 --> 03:22.187
<i>Thought the chances to meet
somebody like you were a million...</i>

03:22.869 --> 03:24.143
l haven't felt this queasy

03:24.189 --> 03:27.101
since my grandpa dragged me
into that shirts and skins b-ball game

03:27.149 --> 03:29.617
at the seniors' centre.

03:29.669 --> 03:32.706
The skin was bouncing
more than the ball.

03:32.749 --> 03:36.628
l could've lived my whole life
without that picture in my head.

03:36.669 --> 03:38.944
You're not actually going
to give this to her, are you?

03:38.989 --> 03:42.106
Of course not.
l'm going to give her this one.

03:43.989 --> 03:49.109
<i>They say that good things take time</i>

03:49.149 --> 03:51.219
<i>But really great things happen...</i>

03:51.269 --> 03:55.547
Wow, a little reverb, some overlay.
Nice.

03:56.709 --> 04:01.066
Daddy called it
''Extreme Mix-over. Lilly Edition.''

04:03.909 --> 04:06.423
Now she'll never know
how unbelievably...

04:06.469 --> 04:09.506
-Hi, hi.
-Completely wonderful she is!

04:09.549 --> 04:11.824
Listen to you, you singer, you!

04:13.829 --> 04:15.103
<i>One in a million...</i>

04:15.149 --> 04:18.937
Oh, my gosh! l'm fantastic!

04:20.469 --> 04:22.664
Almost too good to believe.

04:25.029 --> 04:26.382
But not.

04:27.189 --> 04:29.384
My mom is gonna be so blown away.

04:29.429 --> 04:33.138
l got to tell you, l was a little nervous.
Nobody in my family can really sing.

04:33.189 --> 04:36.022
Yeah, heredity's a powerful thing.

04:38.469 --> 04:40.699
For instance,
my mom's feet always hurt,

04:40.749 --> 04:42.626
and now so do mine.

04:43.309 --> 04:46.346
Hey, why don't you just listen
to the headphones?

04:46.389 --> 04:48.698
You know, get the full effect.

04:50.909 --> 04:53.218
l'm trying to do a nice thing here.

04:53.269 --> 04:55.385
Lilly's happy,
her mom's gonna be happy,

04:55.429 --> 04:56.498
who's it gonna hurt?

04:56.549 --> 04:59.586
<i>You're one in a million...</i>

05:01.589 --> 05:03.659
Any creature with ears.

